codex
The main risk surface is concentrated in `Game.sol`: auction bidding can be manipulated before/after the intended phase, refunds are pushed with an unguarded external call, and final token distribution appears to be sent to the zero address. I’m checking whether any of these overlap so I only report distinct root causes.
codex
One issue is stronger than it first looks: because `claimNft()` and `claim()` only check `isAuctionEnd()`, an attacker can trigger the entire settlement path before `_gameEndTime` ever expires. I’m folding that into a single lifecycle finding rather than splitting it across multiple symptoms.
